---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Yilun Wang" description="About Yilun Wang, NYC-based Organist and Pianist">
  <section class="about">

    <div class="bio-grid">
      <div class="bio-image">
        <!-- Drop your photo as public/about.jpg -->
        <img src="/about.jpg" alt="Yilun Wang" />
      </div>
      <div class="bio-text">
        <h2>About & CV</h2>
        <p>
          Yilun Wang is a multifaceted musician whose artistry spans piano, organ, and harpsichord,
          with more than two decades of performance experience. Celebrated for both technical
          brilliance and expressive sensitivity, she has performed at prestigious venues including
          New York's Cathedral of St. John the Divine, Madison Avenue Presbyterian Church,
          St. Malachy's Church, St. Peter's Church, the Co-Cathedral of St. Joseph, and the
          Basilica of St. Patrick's Old Cathedral, as well as internationally at Beijing's National
          Centre for the Performing Arts, the Bach Haus in Köthen, and Vianden Castle in Luxembourg.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beginning her musical journey at age five, Yilun quickly demonstrated exceptional talent
          and was admitted to the primary division of the Central Conservatory of Music in Beijing,
          where she earned her Bachelor's degree in Piano on full scholarship. She continued her
          education in New York with dual Master's degrees in Classical Organ and Piano at the
          Manhattan School of Music.
        </p>
        <p>
          Her accomplishments include First Prize in the Vienna International Youth Piano Competition,
          Silver Medal at the Royal Academy of Music Aarhus/Aalborg Cup Piano Competition, and the
          Student Commissioning Project Award from The American Guild of Organists (AGO). Currently
          pursuing a Doctor of Musical Arts in Classical Organ, Yilun also serves as organist and
          music teacher at Grace Lutheran Church.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-sections">

      <div class="cv-section">
        <h3>Education</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Doctor of Musical Arts in Classical Organ — Manhattan School of Music</li>
          <li>Master of Music in Classical Organ — Manhattan School of Music</li>
          <li>Master of Music in Classical Piano — Manhattan School of Music</li>
          <li>Bachelor of Arts in Piano — Central Conservatory of Music, Beijing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-section">
        <h3>Experience</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Organist at Grace Lutheran Church</li>
          <li>Student Success Coordinator and Instructor at Manhattan School of Music</li>
          <li>Adjudicator at New York State School Music Association (NYSSMA)</li>
          <li>Part-time Organist at Saint John's in the Village</li>
          <li>Guest Organist at Church of the Holy Apostles</li>
          <li>Substitute Organist at Corpus Christi Catholic Church</li>
          <li>Guest Organist and Pianist at Queensboro Hill Community Church</li>
          <li>Instructor of Piano and Music Theory</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-section">
        <h3>Awards & Scholarships</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>AGO Student Commissioning Project Award Winner (2024)</li>
          <li>AGO Colleague Certification (2023)</li>
          <li>MSM DMA Student Scholarship Recipient (2023–2025)</li>
          <li>MSM International Student Scholarship Recipient (2018–2022)</li>
          <li>First Prize — Vienna International Youth Piano Competition, Beijing (2017)</li>
          <li>Silver Medal — 3rd "Royal Academy of Music Aarhus/Aalborg Cup" Youth Piano Competition (2016)</li>
          <li>Second Place — 13th "Xiwang Cup" Youth Piano Competition (2016)</li>
          <li>Winner — Shenzhen Piano Open Competition (2016)</li>
          <li>Third Prize — 59th International Grotrian-Steinway Klavierspielwettbewerb, Asia-Pacific (2014)</li>
          <li>First Place — 4th China-Tianjin Accordion Festival, Chamber Group (2012)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-section">
        <h3>Selected Performances</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>The Cathedral Church of Saint John the Divine — Sunday Post-Evensong Recital</li>
          <li>Masterclass with Thomas Ospital at Brick Presbyterian Church</li>
          <li>October Organ Recital Series at St. Malachy's – The Actors' Chapel</li>
          <li>NYCAGO End of Season Recital in Honor of Dr. Walter Hilse at Saint Peter's Church</li>
          <li>Organ Fest — Music at Co-Cath</li>
          <li>The Rev. Dr. John Milton Coleman Memorial Organ Recital Series at St. Philip's Episcopal Church</li>
          <li>Italian Organ Music Masterclass with Eugenio Maria Fagiani</li>
          <li>Five Historic Erben Pipe Organ Concerts for Make Music Day 2022</li>
          <li>Harpsichord Recital at Rahm Hall, Manhattan School of Music</li>
          <li>Manhattan School of Music Symphony Orchestra Opening Concert at Neidorff-Karpati Hall</li>
          <li>J.S. Bach Johannes-Passion at the Co-Cathedral of St. Joseph, Brooklyn</li>
          <li>Telemann-Sonntagsmusiken in Magdeburg, Germany</li>
          <li>Early music concert at the Bach House in Köthen, Germany</li>
          <li>Hehe Quintet at the National Centre for the Performing Arts, Beijing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-section">
        <h3>Teachers</h3>
        <div class="teachers-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="teacher-category">Organ</p>
            <p>Walter Hilse, Andrew Henderson, Raymond Nagem, Katherine Meloan</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="teacher-category">Piano</p>
            <p>Yafen Zhu, Yuan Ling, Ling Zhao, Pingguo Zhao, Solomon Mikowsky, Inesa Sinkevych, Alexander Korsantia, Tamás Ungár, Kun Sing Lee, Jin Jü, Wei-Yi Yang</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="teacher-category">Harpsichord</p>
            <p>Jocelyn Stewart, Kenneth Cooper, Avi Stein</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="teacher-category">Conducting</p>
            <p>Maureen Hynes, Ronald Oliver Jr., Oliver Hagen</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cv-section">
        <h3>Summer Festivals</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Oregon Bach Festival</li>
          <li>Euro Art in Halle, Germany</li>
          <li>International Baroque Academy 2019 in Oberaudorf, Germany</li>
          <li>Study Tour — Royal Academy of Music Aarhus/Aalborg, Hochschule für Musik und Theater Hamburg, Fontys School of Fine and Performing Arts</li>
          <li>Vianden International Music Festival</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .bio-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .bio-image img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .bio-text h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .bio-text p {
    color: #333;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .cv-sections {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cv-section h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .cv-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cv-section ul li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #333;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .cv-section ul li::before {
    content: '–';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .teachers-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem 2rem;
  }

  .teacher-category {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem !important;
  }

  .teachers-grid p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .bio-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .bio-image img {
      max-width: 260px;
    }

    .teachers-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
